Optimizer Capabilities:
  - store-recall-peephole: active; Elides immediate X->П r / П->X r pairs when no exact-machine effect is crossed.
  - stack-current-x-scheduling: active; Keeps a just-computed value in X for a following commutative use and removes the temporary store after data-flow proof.
  - tail-call-lowering: active; Replaces subroutine calls in tail position with direct jumps so rule factoring and terminal branches do not force extra returns or branch hops.
  - return-zero-jump: candidate; Uses В/О as one-cell БП 01 only when the return stack is known empty.
  - vo-return-body-reorder: candidate; Candidate: reorder HEAD/MAIN/SUB so a subroutine return lands at the program head and a ПП/В/О pair collapses. Single-use procedures are already inlined and tail-position calls already become direct jumps, so the remaining gain needs a global layout search with no proven safe trigger on the current programs.
  - super-number-deferred-normalization: candidate; Candidate: keep an un-normalized super-number (extra hidden mantissa digits) to defer a range/error check. The reference emulator models only the 8 visible mantissa digits, so the hidden-digit behavior the idiom relies on cannot be reproduced or safely proven, and no language construct produces it.
  - packed-position-type: candidate; Candidate: a language-level packed position type N.0000H carrying an integer position plus packed (hex) fractional sub-coordinates. The dual-use round-trip (К [x] recovers the position, К {x} recovers the packed fraction) is already exploited by constants-dual-use; a dedicated type would only add language surface that no current program consumes.
  - coord-list-scaled-decimal: candidate; Stores 10x10 board coordinates as y.x decimal values when all visible uses allow it, so row/column/diagonal scans avoid repeated /10 digit extraction.
  - dual-constant-sign-digit: candidate; Candidate: a language intent for a dual constant 1.|-00 plus compact sign-digits (2N..9N) and their comparison semantics. The negative-zero comparison behavior is already active through the negative-zero-threshold family; no current program needs the additional sign-digit literal surface.
  - branch-removal: candidate; Umbrella rule for replacing provably equivalent conditionals with branchless arithmetic, sign, extrema, or masked updates.
  - zero-condition-test: active; Uses direct F x?0 tests when one side of a condition is a proved zero, avoiding a zero literal and subtraction.
  - dispatch-compare-chain: active; Lowers high-level command dispatch automatically; small proven dispatches may use indirect or super-dark dispatch.

